From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Spencer Bull <spencerbull@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 2026 14:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drm/i915/psr: handle Panel Replay full-line x granularity

DP specifies that Panel Replay selective-update X granularity value
0xffff means full-line granularity. v6.19 treats the raw value as a
literal width, which can mis-handle Panel Replay selective update on
panels that advertise full-line updates this way.

Translate the sentinel to the current horizontal display width before
running the granularity check.

Adapted from upstream commit a99cac460dde (drm/i915/psr: Fix for
Panel Replay X granularity DPCD register handling).
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c | 5 +++++
 include/drm/display/drm_dp.h             | 1 +
 2 files changed, 6 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
@@ -1312,9 +1312,12 @@
 	const int crtc_hdisplay = crtc_state->hw.adjusted_mode.crtc_hdisplay;
 	const int crtc_vdisplay = crtc_state->hw.adjusted_mode.crtc_vdisplay;
 	u16 y_granularity = 0;
+	u16 sink_w_granularity = intel_dp->psr.su_w_granularity ==
+		DP_PANEL_REPLAY_FULL_LINE_GRANULARITY ?
+		crtc_hdisplay : intel_dp->psr.su_w_granularity;
 
 	/* PSR2 HW only send full lines so we only need to validate the width */
-	if (crtc_hdisplay % intel_dp->psr.su_w_granularity)
+	if (crtc_hdisplay % sink_w_granularity)
 		return false;
 
 	if (crtc_vdisplay % intel_dp->psr.su_y_granularity)
--- a/include/drm/display/drm_dp.h
+++ b/include/drm/display/drm_dp.h
@@ -572,6 +572,7 @@
 
 #define DP_PANEL_REPLAY_CAP_X_GRANULARITY		0xb2
 #define DP_PANEL_REPLAY_CAP_Y_GRANULARITY		0xb4
+#define DP_PANEL_REPLAY_FULL_LINE_GRANULARITY		0xffff
 
 /* Link Configuration */
 #define	DP_LINK_BW_SET		            0x100
